Rating: 0
I wanted to comment just on the Muhammara. Traditionally, it's made without water and has olive oil, chopped walnuts, raw minced garlic, pomegranate molasses, and sumac spice. Just combine the roasted red peppers, a good dash of olive oil, and the remaining ingredients in a food processor and pulse a couple times. It's much tastier than the recipe here. Good luck!!

