Rating: 4
I'm rating this 4 forks with the reviewer recommended modifications of using the other Muhammara recipe & adding garlic to the yogurt sauce. Those are both so good that I've made them 3 times for other recipes. I had a little Muhammara left and some grilled eggplant and pureed those together & it was delicious as a dip or spread on flatbread. I think there is a typo in this recipe. 3 Tbsp of paprika turned these into Hungarian meatballs. Chicken Paprikash doesn't even have that much!! No one mentions this so maybe it was just that my paprika was new but I would say 2 teaspoons or 1 Tbsp would be more like it, most Kofte recipes don't have any. So basically I love this recipe because thanks to reviewers who changed everything about it & using less paprika turns the whole thing into a new recipe that's GREAT!!

